column1: #Text=County Kerry ( Irish : Contae Chiarraí ) , in Southwest Ireland , is regarded as perhaps the most scenic county in Ireland and is certainly the most renowned for its scenery .
#Text=It holds most of Ireland 's highest mountains ( including the highest , Carrauntuohill ) in its most westerly fringes and holds a special place in Irish culture .
#Text=It became a popular tourist attraction in the 19th century and is still very popular today , despite considerable rainfall .
#Text=In some places the tourist pressure has arguably had a mixed effect but in general the county is friendly and relaxed as well as beautiful .
#Text=( Oileán Ciarraí , " people of Ciar 's island " )
#Text=( An Daingean or Daingean Uí Chúis , " Ó Cúis ' fort " )
#Text=( Lios Tuathail , " Tuathal 's ringfort " ) has a 13th C castle .

column1: #Text=( Trá Lí , " strand of the Lee ( river ) " ) – county town
#Text=( Abhainn an Scáil or Abha na Scáil )
#Text=are six little islands off the Dingle peninsula , inhabited solely by Irish-speakers until 1953 but then evacuated .
#Text=Boat trips to the largest , Great Blasket , run from Dunquin on the peninsula , where a visitor centre describes their lives .
#Text=( An Fearann Fuar , " the cold land " )
#Text=( Mórchuaird Chiarraí ) – A scenic route around the Iveragh peninsula .
#Text=( Sceilig Mhichíl ) – A small island off the coast , granted UNESCO World Heritage status in 1996 .
#Text=English is the most spoken language , however , in certain parts of Kerry such as in Dingle , Irish is the living language spoken by up to 70 % of the locals .

#Text=There is the small Kerry Airport ( KIR ) at Farranfore , between Tralee and Killarney served by Ryanair and summer charters and this has regularly scheduled flights to Dublin , " London"- Stansted , " London"- Luton , Manchester , Lorient and " Frankfurt"- Hahn .
#Text=However , Kerry is easily connected to Cork Airport , which serves more destinations , and also Shannon Airport near by .
#Text=( Flights to USA , Canada and the rest of Europe , including Paris CDG . )
#Text=There is a regular rail service to Killarney , Farranfore and Tralee from Dublin and Cork and there are connections from all stations in Ireland .
#Text=See the Irish Rail website for timetables
#Text=If coming from Clare or Galway there is a car ferry across the Shannon estuary between Killimer ( Clare ) and Tarbert ( Kerry ) which can save driving and is a scenic route .
#Text=It departs hourly all year-round and every half hour in Summer from both sides .
#Text=The ferry crosses the mouth of the river Shannon as it enters the Atlantic and dolphins are commonly seen from the ferry
#Text=Bus Eireann runs regular bus services to and within Kerry .
#Text=Walking - the Kerry Way is a major network of marked trails .
#Text=There are numerous major and local car rental companies that have locations in County Kerry .
#Text=Most will have rental desks in Kerry airport Killarney town or both .
#Text=Avis - car rental depot located within Shannon Airport
#Text=Budget Car Rental Ireland - desks in both Kerry Airport and Killarney town .
#Text=The Ring of Kerry is the best known area of natural beauty in Ireland .
#Text=It is a 120 mile circuit around the Iveragh Peninsula in south Kerry passing through Killarney , Killorglin , Glenbeigh , Caherciveen , Waterville , Sneem and Kenmare .
#Text=It is the dominant sport in Kerry and the county team has won more All-Ireland Senior Football Championships than any other .
#Text=As anywhere else in Ireland , there are many bed and breakfasts ( B&B ) in Kerry and around the Ring of Kerry .
#Text=They are all priced about the same , which is € 35 per person during the summer .
